\f0\b\fs48 \cf0 SYMPTOMS vs DISEASES\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\slleading24\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs28 \cf0 \
\
I had a friend one day at work get frustrated with our bosses ineptitude to address an employee. The leaderships solution was half hearted and naive at best. He looked at me and said, "It's like putting a bandaid on cancer!". It was true, the issue was never really addressed, and the company suffered more than it should.\
\
That image always stuck with me. Putting a bandaid on cancer may cover it up what you see, but it doesn't change what's going on. It may even make you feel better in the moment, but it won't heal anything long term. It may even cure the patch of skin that was a problem, but we all know there is still something lurking inside of the body that will eventually come up again.\
\
If all you do is deal with the symptoms your body is going through you'll never get rid of the disease. This may seem obvious but - we should be treating the disease and not the symptoms. If all you do is put a bandaid on cancer, eventually it will kill you. The only way to heal from cancer is to deal with it directly and make sure you get it all.\
\
As a culture there are not many who play around with cancer because we know how deadly it is. But what we intuitively get when it comes to 
\f0\b physical
\f1\b0  
\f0\b health
\f1\b0  we miss it when it comes to 
\f0\b emotional
\f1\b0  and 
\f0\b spiritual
\f1\b0  
\f0\b health
\f1\b0 . \
\
So what does it look like to spiritually treat the symptoms and not the disease? (need better examples)\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li720\fi-720\slleading24\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}It's the person who has a problem with greed but thinks if they just get on a budget they'll be ok.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}It's the person who has a problem with lust but thinks it is a porn or sex issue\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}It's the person who has a problem with laziness but believes if they can just find the right schedule or hustle more they'll be good\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}It's the person who has a problem with gluttony but thinks if they can find the right diet then they'll be ok\
\pard\tx560\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\slleading24\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
Maybe that is what you've been doing. Maybe you never thought about it like this. Maybe, if you can shift to dealing with the diseases in your life instead of the symptoms you can start to see real growth. \
\
\
\

\f0\b\fs48 WHY vs WHAT\

\f1\b0\fs28 \
But how do you know which is which? How can you tell if what you are fighting is a symptom or a disease? \
\
It's easier than you might think. \
\
It's as simple as separating 
\f0\b WHAT
\f1\b0  you do from 
\f0\b WHY
\f1\b0  you do it. \
\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\slleading24\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Think about it, the person who struggles with credit card debt spends more money than they make...but why? We live in a country and a time where we have more than any other generation ever to live. The cheapest new car you can buy today is light years ahead of the cars from 100 years ago and don't get me started on the fact that we HAVE CARS!!!!\
\
Or the person who has some type of addiction. Maybe they struggles with pornography and continue to look and look at more and more images only feeling full or content for a few moments at a time, then pursuing something more, something new, something they haven't seen yet. But why? What is that drive that is in them to do that and where does it come from. Simply putting a filter on a phone or computer might stop a behavior for a time period but there is still this desire that hasn't been dealt with.\
\
Or maybe you're the person who continually is looking for what's next and never 
\f2\i feeling
\f1\i0  satisfied. You go from relationship to relationship...and then sometimes back to an old relationship hoping it will be different this time. Maybe you hop from job to job always thinking it is the job. Thinking it is 
\f0\b WHAT
\f1\b0  you are doing and never stepping back and asking a deeper question about 
\f0\b WHY
\f1\b0  we work.\
\
Why do we stay stuck though? What is holding us back? We focus on WHAT instead of WHY? We believe that if we can just change WHAT we do then we'll be able to move forward and be healthier, happier, and more whole.\
\
But if we do not deal with the deeper issue of WHY, we simply give up one bad habit and find another, we swap one addiction for another, we go from one bad relationship to the next. It's the person who gives up smoking only to develop a deeper taste for food and becomes addicted to food. They might be a little healthier but they are still stuck. 
\f0\b Stuck in a pattern they can't seem to get out of because of a disease they can't see.\

\f1\b0 \
\
