\f0\b\fs48 JESUS AND WORSHIP\

\f1\b0\fs28 \
There is a story in the Gospel of Mark where some religious leaders asked Jesus a very important question.  In the 12th chapter one of the religious leaders asked Him "What is the most important commandment?". This may not seem like a hard question to answer but at that point in the nation of Israel there were 633 commands to live by. That's a lot to keep track of. There were rules and regulations for anything and everything in a persons life. And every one of them felt important because for the religious person every one of them were from God.\
\
It would have been easy for Jesus to say "All of them". If God said it, that settles it. They're all God's word, they're all important, you should follow all of them. If it wasn't important to God then He wouldn't have had it written down. \
\
But that's not what Jesus does. He looks at all of the Old Testament writings.  He scans all 39 books that cover 929 chapters and says there is one thing that is more important than everything else. He said it this way:\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
