\f1\b0\fs28 \cf0 \
If you show up to any alligator feeding pin you'll see dozens if not hundreds of alligators. But there are always a few that stand out. They are the old ones, the wise ones, the ones that have survived the longest and ate the best. Those are the ones that even have names...names like Fred.\
\
As we navigate a world full of alligators we're tempted to feed, I want us to focus on a specific few. And not just any random few. The deep seeded ones that like the alligators, have been around for thousands of years. These are the issues that are deep seeded. The root causes of so many of our problems. In fact, almost every issue you struggle with can be traced back to just a small few. \
\
(1)Evagrius Ponticus was a monk in the fourth century who first highlight these. He referred to them as the "eight evil thoughts".  In his mind there were deep seated thoughts that ultimately lead to all of the problems that show up in our lives and if we could just deal with these eight then we would be able to get rid of a lot of pain and suffering in our worlds.\
\
What were evil eight? Gluttony, lust, avarice, anger, sloth, sadness, vainglory, and pride. \
\
If you're like me you might have to look a few of those words up. But don't worry, over time a few were tweaked, combined, renamed, rebranded and eventually named "The 7 Deadly Sins". \
\
